  "statement": {
    "markdown": "You are given an array of integers that needs to be sorted in non‑decreasing order using the recursive version of Insertion Sort. In the recursive approach, the problem is broken down by first sorting the first N‑1 elements recursively and then inserting the N‑th element into its correct position among the sorted prefix.\n\nYour task is to implement this algorithm and output the sorted array.\n\n**Input Format**\n- The first line contains a single integer **N**, the number of elements in the array.\n- The second line contains **N** space‑separated integers – the elements of the array.\n\n**Output Format**\n- Print a single line with the **N** sorted integers in non‑decreasing order, separated by a single space.\n\n**Constraints**\n- 1 ≤ N ≤ 1000\n- -1000000 ≤ each array element ≤ 1000000\n\n**Notes**\n- The recursion depth will be at most N, which fits comfortably within typical recursion limits for the given constraints.\n- You must implement the sorting using recursion; iterative solutions will not be accepted.\n",
    "inputFormat": "The first line contains an integer N, the size of the array.\nThe second line contains N space-separated integers representing the array elements.",
    "outputFormat": "A single line with N space-separated integers sorted in non‑decreasing order.",
